defaultIn common with a Cycle Audit a Safety A
defaultudit is a structured process
default. However, it
default looks only at the safety aspects of changes to the 
defaulthighway. It is 
defaultnot obliged to offer suggestions as how the highway might be improved as a means of encouraging more cycling.
default 
defaultWhilst this may ensure 
defaultcyclist safety
default,
default it does not achieve the key objectives of 
defaulta Cycle Audit which is to look at
default the scheme to “ensure that oppo
defaultrtunities to encourage cycling are consider
defaulted
default and that cycling conditions are not inadvertently made worse”.
default Opportunities might include exempting cyclists from a banned turn or road closure. 
defaultS
defaulttop
defaultping
default conditions becoming worse 
defaultmight involve i
defaultntroducing a s
defaultignal controlled junction instead of a roundabout on a route on which cycling is to be encouraged
default. This solution would 
defaultremove a disincentive to cycling and
default improve cycle safety
default.
